Gebhardt
Gebhardt is a manufacturer of roof bases, as mentioned in the context of installing roof fans.<SEP>Gebhardt is an organization that should be consulted regarding motor suitability for more than three starts per hour.<SEP>Gebhardt is a manufacturer of ventilation systems and components, as indicated by the reference to using only original Gebhardt spare parts. The text warns against using non-original parts, implying Gebhardt's role as a supplier.<SEP>Gebhardt is mentioned in relation to the 'Socle de toiture Gebhardt' (roof base).<SEP>Gebhardt is an organization that should be consulted regarding the suitability of motors when there are more than three starts per hour.<SEP>Gebhardt is a manufacturer of roof fans that emphasizes safety and quality. They provide a guarantee that is invalidated by unauthorized modifications to their fans and accept no liability for damage resulting from disregarding the operating manual.<SEP>Gebhardt is the manufacturer of the ventilators, and they disclaim responsibility for damages resulting from failure to follow the assembly instructions.

Qualified Personnel
Individuals with the necessary training and expertise to perform installations and assembly work safely and correctly, in accordance with regulations.<SEP>Qualified Personnel should perform visual and functional checks on the fan at regular intervals.<SEP>Qualified personnel refers to individuals who are trained and authorized to install, operate, and service the fans to ensure safety and prevent damage.

Electricity Supply Companies
These are the companies responsible for providing electricity to the installation site and ensuring electrical safety regulations are followed.

IEC 364
IEC 364 is an international standard related to electrical installations in buildings, aiming to ensure safety and proper functioning.<SEP>IEC 364 is an international standard related to electrical installations.

DIN VDE 0100
DIN VDE 0100 is a German standard equivalent to IEC 364 for electrical installations.<SEP>DIN VDE 0100 is a German standard equivalent to IEC 364, concerning electrical installations in buildings.

DIN 57105-1
DIN 57105-1 / VDE 0105-1 is a German standard related to the operation of electrical installations.<SEP>DIN 57105-1 is a German standard related to the operation of electrical installations, addressing safety during operation.

VDE 0105-1
VDE 0105-1 is a German standard equivalent to DIN 57105-1, focusing on safety during the operation of electrical installations.<SEP>VDE 0105-1 is a German standard related to the operation of electrical installations.

IN EN 60204-1
IN EN 60204-1 is a standard related to the safety of machinery, specifically electrical equipment of machines.

VDE 0113-1
VDE 0113-1 is a German standard equivalent to DIN EN 60204-1 for the safety of machinery and electrical equipment.<SEP>VDE 0113-1 is a German standard equivalent to IN EN 60204-1, concerning the safety of electrical equipment in machines.

pr EN 50154
pr EN 50154 is a standard related to electrical apparatus for potentially explosive atmospheres.

VDE 0165
VDE 0165 is a German standard that covers electrical installations in areas with explosion hazards.

Roof Fans
Roof fans are ventilation devices designed to be installed on rooftops to provide air circulation and exhaust.

Base Frame
The base frame is a structural component of the roof fan, designed with a wide projection and holes for fixing the fan to a base or roof structure.<SEP>The structure upon which the roof fan is fitted. The base plate of the fan is designed for direct fitting on a base frame.

Roof Base
The roof base is the structure or foundation onto which the roof fan is mounted and secured. Gebhardt manufactures roof bases.

Connecting Cable
The connecting cable is the electrical cable used to connect the roof fan to the power supply, as referenced in the installation instructions.

Electrical Installation
The electrical installation refers to the process of connecting the roof fan to the electrical power supply, ensuring it adheres to safety standards and regulations.

Terminal Box
The terminal box is an enclosure or housing that contains the electrical terminals for connecting the motor of the roof fan to the power supply.

Control Switch
The control switch is a device used to turn the roof fan on or off and potentially control its speed or other functions.

Electrical Impacts
Electrical impacts refer to the potential for electrical shocks or injuries resulting from improper electrical installation or handling of the roof fan.

Motor
Motor is a component of the fan that requires periodic maintenance and inspection.<SEP>The motor is the electrical component of the roof fan that drives the impeller to generate airflow.<SEP>The part of the fan that provides power for rotation

Wiring Diagram
The wiring diagram is a schematic illustration that shows how to properly connect the electrical wires to the motor of the roof fan.

Impeller
The Impeller is the rotating part of the fan. It must be checked for free movement and should not be touched when turning.<SEP>The impeller is the rotating component of the roof fan that generates airflow when the motor is running.

Ducting
Ducting refers to the system of ducts or pipes that are connected to the roof fan to channel and direct airflow to specific locations.

Gebhardt-Roof Base
A specific type of roof base manufactured by Gebhardt, designed for secure and stable mounting of roof fans.

DV 30
A model or type of roof fan with specific connection instructions.<SEP>DV 30 is a type of fan requiring specific procedures for motor impeller removal.<SEP>DV 30 is a specific model or type of fan. The text provides instructions for disassembling the motor-turbine of this model.<SEP>DV 30 is a model of Dachventilator with a specified operating temperature range.<SEP>DV 30 refers to a specific model of ventilator.<SEP>Model of ventilator.<SEP>DV 30 is a specific model of the fan with instructions for disassembly.<SEP>DV 30 is a model series of Wolf Dachventilatoren, featuring a housing and base frame made of galvanized sheet steel.<SEP>DV 30 is a specific series of ventilators with features such as a galvanized steel cap and base, air inlet flange, and aerodynamically designed grille.

DV 40 to DV 125
A range of roof fan models with specific connection instructions.<SEP>DV 40 to DV 125 are types of fans requiring specific procedures for motor impeller removal, different from DV 30.

IEC 364 / DIN VDE 0100
An international/German standard related to electrical installations in buildings, aiming to ensure safety and proper functioning.<SEP>IEC 364 / DIN VDE 0100 is an electrical standard that must be followed during electrical installation.

DIN 57105-1 / VDE 0105-1
DIN 57105-1 / VDE 0105-1 is an electrical standard that must be followed during electrical installation.<SEP>German standards related to the operation of electrical installations, addressing safety during operation.

IN EN 60204-1 / VDE 0113-1
A standard related to the safety of machinery, specifically electrical equipment of machines.

pr EN 50154 / VDE 0165
A standard related to electrical apparatus for potentially explosive atmospheres.<SEP>pr EN 50154 / VDE 0165 is an electrical standard that must be followed for Ex-type ventilators.

Warping
Deformation of the base or structure, leading to bearing damage and fatigue fractures

Plant Parts
Components or machinery connected to the fan which may transmit forces or vibrations.

Adjustable Connecting Sleeves
Flexible sleeves that connect the fan to ducting, minimizing vibration transfer.

Protective Devices
Safety equipment that should be replaced after assembly work.

Wolf GmbH
Wolf GmbH is a company located in Mainburg, Germany, responsible for drawing up the declaration of conformity for the Roof extract fan DV.<SEP>Wolf GmbH is a company located in Mainburg, Germany, that provides roof extract fans and related services. Contact information includes a phone number, fax number, and website.<SEP>Wolf GmbH is the issuer of the EG Conformity Declaration, located at Industriestraße 1, D-84048 Mainburg. They manufacture the Dachventilator DV.<SEP>Wolf GmbH is the issuer of the declaration of conformity, located in Mainburg, Germany.<SEP>Wolf GmbH is a company located in Mainburg, Germany, specializing in heating technology. Their contact information includes a phone number, fax number, and website.<SEP>Wolf GmbH is a company located in Mainburg, Germany, specializing in heating technology and manufacturing Dachventilatoren DV.<SEP>Wolf GmbH is a company located in Mainburg, Germany, specializing in heating technology.

Mainburg
Mainburg is a city in Germany where Wolf GmbH is located.<SEP>Mainburg is a town in Germany where Wolf GmbH is located, as indicated by the postal code 84048.<SEP>Mainburg is a town in Germany, specifically D-84048 Mainburg, where Wolf GmbH is located.<SEP>Mainburg is a town in Germany where Wolf GmbH is located.<SEP>Mainburg is a town in Germany, specifically identified by the postal code 84048, where Wolf GmbH is located.<SEP>Mainburg is a town in Germany where Wolf GmbH is located, specifically at Postfach 1380, 84048 Mainburg.<SEP>Mainburg is a town in Germany where Wolf GmbH is located.

Michael Epple
Michael Epple is responsible for documentation at Wolf GmbH, located at Industriestraße 1, D-84048 Mainburg.<SEP>Michael Epple is responsible for the documentation related to the declaration of conformity.<SEP>Michael Epple is the person responsible for the documentation at Wolf GmbH.

Gerdewan Jacobs
Gerdewan Jacobs is a Director at Wolf GmbH.<SEP>Gerdewan Jacobs is a manager at Wolf GmbH.<SEP>Gerdewan Jacobs is the Geschäftsführer (Managing Director) of Wolf GmbH.

Dachventilator DV
Dachventilator DV is the product manufactured by Wolf GmbH, for which the EG Conformity Declaration is issued.

Maschinenrichtlinie 2006/42/EG
Maschinenrichtlinie 2006/42/EG is a directive related to machinery safety, cited in the EG Conformity Declaration.

Niederspannungsrichtlinie 2006/95/EG
Niederspannungsrichtlinie 2006/95/EG is a low voltage directive cited in the EG Conformity Declaration.

EMV-Richtlinie 2004/108/EG
EMV-Richtlinie 2004/108/EG is an EMC (Electromagnetic Compatibility) directive cited in the EG Conformity Declaration.

DIN EN ISO 12100
DIN EN ISO 12100 is a standard for the safety of machinery, covering general design principles.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 12100 outlines basic concepts and general principles for the design of safe machinery.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 12100 is a standard related to the safety of machinery.

DIN EN ISO 13857
A safety standard related to guards protecting against contact with the impeller, ensuring operator safety. Required for installation if there is a risk of contact with the impeller.<SEP>A safety standard related to guards protecting against contact with the impeller.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 is a safety standard related to protective devices for ventilation systems.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 is a standard for safety distances to prevent reaching hazard zones with upper and lower limbs.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 is a standard related to safety distances to prevent hazards from machinery, specifically regarding the installation of protective grids.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 specifies safety distances to prevent hazard zones from being reached by upper and lower limbs.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 refers to safety standards for protection systems, particularly concerning access to ventilation components. Protection systems are required to prevent access to dangerous parts of the machine.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 is a standard related to safety measures, specifically concerning protection against hazards from machinery.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 is a standard related to safety guards for fan inlet openings.<SEP>DIN EN ISO 13857 is a standard related to safety distances to prevent access to dangerous zones in machinery.

DIN EN 349
DIN EN 349 defines minimum gaps to avoid crushing of parts of the human body by machinery.<SEP>DIN EN 349 is a standard for minimum gaps to avoid crushing body parts.<SEP>DIN EN 349 is a standard related to minimum gaps to prevent crushing risks in machinery.

DIN EN 60204-1
DIN EN 60204-1 / VDE 0113-1 is a European standard for the safety of machinery and electrical equipment.<SEP>DIN EN 60204-1 addresses the safety of machinery's electrical equipment.<SEP>DIN EN 60204-1 is a standard for the electrical equipment of machinery.<SEP>DIN EN 60204-1 is a standard related to the electrical equipment of machinery.

DIN EN 60730
DIN EN 60730 Standard related to automatic electrical controls.<SEP>DIN EN 60730 covers automatic electrical controls for household and similar use.<SEP>DIN EN 60730 is a standard for automatic electrical controls.<SEP>DIN EN 60730 is a standard related to automatic electrical controls.

DIN EN 61000-6-2
DIN EN 61000-6-2 is a standard for electromagnetic compatibility.<SEP>DIN EN 61000-6-2 specifies electromagnetic compatibility (EMC) requirements.<SEP>DIN EN 61000-6-2 is a standard related to electromagnetic compatibility.

DIN EN 61000-6-3
DIN EN 61000-6-3 is a standard for electromagnetic compatibility.<SEP>DIN EN 61000-6-3 specifies electromagnetic compatibility (EMC) requirements.<SEP>DIN EN 61000-6-3 is a standard related to electromagnetic compatibility.

EG-Konformitätserklärung
EG-Konformitätserklärung is the German term for EC Declaration of Conformity, indicating that a product meets EU standards.

Industriestraße 1
Industriestraße 1 is the street address of Wolf GmbH in Mainburg, Germany.<SEP>Industriestraße 1, D-84048 Mainburg, is the address of Wolf GmbH.<SEP>The street address of Wolf GmbH in Mainburg, Germany.

D-84048 Mainburg
D-84048 Mainburg is the postal code and city of Wolf GmbH's location in Germany.<SEP>The postal code and town where Wolf GmbH is located.

Maschinenrichtlinie 2006/42/EG, Anhang II 1.A
This refers to the Machinery Directive 2006/42/EC, Annex II 1.A, a European Union directive related to machinery safety. This directive outlines the essential health and safety requirements for the design and manufacture of machinery.

Postfach 1380
PO Box address of Wolf GmbH in Mainburg, Germany.<SEP>Postfach 1380 is the PO box address of Wolf GmbH.

www.wolf-heiztechnik.de
www.wolf-heiztechnik.de is the website address of Wolf GmbH.

2006 - 05
Issue date of Maschinenrichtlinie 2006/42/EG.<SEP>The Edition Date of the Directive 2006/42/EG.

2006 - 12
Issue date of Niederspannungsrichtlinie 2006/95/EG.<SEP>The Edition Date of the Directive 2006/95/EG.

2004 - 12
Issue date of EMV-Richtlinie 2004/108/EG.<SEP>The Edition Date of the Directive 2004/108/EG.

2011 - 03
Issue date of DIN EN ISO 12100.<SEP>The Edition Date of the DIN EN ISO 12100 Standard.

2008 - 06
Issue date of DIN EN ISO 13857.<SEP>The Edition Date of the DIN EN ISO 13857 Standard.

2009 - 01
Issue date of DIN EN 349.<SEP>The Edition Date of the DIN EN 349 Standard.

2007 - 06
Issue date of DIN EN 60204-1.<SEP>The Edition Date of the DIN EN 60204-1 Standard.

2009 - 06
Issue date of DIN EN 60730.<SEP>The Edition Date of the DIN EN 60730 Standard.

2011 - 06
Issue date of DIN EN 61000-6-2.<SEP>The Edition Date of the DIN EN 61000-6-2 Standard.

2011 - 09
Issue date of DIN EN 61000-6-3.<SEP>The Edition Date of the DIN EN 61000-6-3 Standard.

Wolf
An organization that manufactures roof fans and disclaims liability for any injury or damage to property resulting from improper use of their products.<SEP>An organization that manufactures roof fans and disclaims liability for improper use of their products.<SEP>Wolf is a company that manufactures Dachventilatoren and does not take responsibility for damages resulting from improper use.<SEP>Wolf is a manufacturer or provider of the extractors de toiture (roof extractors), and is mentioned in the context of liability for damages resulting from non-conforming use.<SEP>Wolf is the manufacturer of the Série DV 40 à DV 125 series of roof extractors.<SEP>Wolf is the manufacturer of the motor, requiring confirmation of motor suitability for more than three starts per hour.<SEP>Wolf is a manufacturer of Dachventilatoren (roof ventilators) and provides operating instructions. They emphasize safety and quality, and disclaim liability for damages resulting from non-compliance with the instructions or unauthorized modifications.

DIN 24 155-2
A standard specification for flange connections at the intake of the roof fan, ensuring compatibility and secure attachment.<SEP>A standard specification for flange connections at the intake of the roof fan.<SEP>DIN 24 155-2 is a standard for flange connections, relevant to the air inlet of the extractors.<SEP>DIN 24 155-2 is a standard for flanges used in ventilation systems.<SEP>DIN 24 155-2 is a standard that specifies flange connections, which are used in the intake of DV fans.<SEP>DIN 24 155-2 is a standard specifying flange connections for the ventilators, ensuring compatibility with other equipment.<SEP>DIN 24 155-2 is a standard for the connection of flanges at the air inlet of the ventilators.

DV 40
A series of roof fans with ZDH silencer casing made of galvanised sheet steel.<SEP>A series of roof fans with ZDH silencer casing made of galvanised sheet steel. Suitable for extraction of dust-free air and non-aggressive gases or vapours, with a permissible transport media temperature range of -20°C to +40°C (up to +60°C with specific identification plate).<SEP>DV 40 is a model number for roof extractors, specifying temperature limits of -20°C to +40°C.<SEP>DV 40 is a model of Dachventilator with a specified operating temperature range.<SEP>DV 40 refers to a specific model of ventilator.

DV 125
A series of roof fans with ZDH silencer casing made of galvanised sheet steel.<SEP>A series of roof fans with ZDH silencer casing made of galvanised sheet steel. Suitable for extraction of dust-free air and non-aggressive gases or vapours, with a permissible transport media temperature range of -20°C to +40°C.<SEP>DV 125 is a model number for roof extractors, specifying temperature limits of -20°C to +40°C.<SEP>DV 125 is a specific model or type of fan, similar to DV 30. Disassembly instructions are provided.<SEP>DV 125 is a model of Dachventilator with a specified operating temperature range.<SEP>DV 125 refers to a specific model of ventilator.

ZDH
A silencer casing feature for DV 40 and DV 125 series, made of galvanised sheet steel, contributing to noise reduction during fan operation.<SEP>A silencer casing feature for DV 40 and DV 125 series, made of galvanised sheet steel.<SEP>Possibly an organization related to the DV 40 bis DV 125 models, but its specific nature isn't detailed in the text.<SEP>ZDH is likely the manufacturer or a company associated with the DV 40 to 125 product.<SEP>ZDH is mentioned in the context of a DV 40 to 125 fan maintenance guide.<SEP>ZDH refers to a variant of the DV 40 and DV 125 extractors, specifying temperature limits of -20°C to +40°C.<SEP>ZDH is related to DV 40 à DV 125.<SEP>ZDH appears in the model designation 'DV 40 à 125 - ZDH', and it's a sub-model or a variant. Disassembly instructions are provided.

Europe
Implied, extractors are produced in Europe due to the presence of the French language

Série DV 40 à DV 125
A series of roof extractors, with specific models ranging from DV 40 to DV 125, featuring a galvanized steel housing.<SEP>The group of roof extractors made by Wolf

Caisson Silencieux
A soundproof housing made of galvanized sheet steel, designed to reduce noise from the extractor.

Tôle Acier Galvanisé
Galvanized steel sheet metal used in the construction of the soundproof housing for the roof extractors.

Embase
A base with an air inlet bell made of galvanized steel, prepared for mounting on a frame with overhangs for integrating roof insulation.

Pavillon d’entrée d’air
An air inlet bell made of galvanized steel, part of the base.

Acier Galvanisé
Acier galvanisé (Galvanized Steel) refers to the type of steel used in the construction of the ventilator components, providing corrosion resistance.<SEP>Galvanized steel used in the construction of the base and air inlet bell.

Grille Anti-Volatile
A bird screen placed in the discharge section to prevent birds or debris from entering.<SEP>Grille anti-volatile (Anti-Volatile Grid) refers to the grid placed in the exhaust section to prevent debris from entering the ventilator.

Section de Refoulement
The discharge section where air exits the extractor and where the bird screen is placed.

Turbine à Réaction
A reaction turbine directly mounted on the rotor of an integrated motor.

Moteur Intégré
An integrated motor that directly drives the reaction turbine, featuring variable speed and anti-vibration mounts.<SEP>Moteur intégré (Integrated Motor) refers to the motor built into the ventilator, featuring variable speed and thermal contacts for protection.

Thermo Contacts
Devices implemented in the motor windings to protect the motor against overheating.<SEP>Thermal contacts embedded in the winding of the integrated motor to provide thermal protection.

Tourelle
A complete roof extractor unit ready to be mounted, featuring a service switch under the cover.<SEP>Tourelle (Turret) refers to the housing of the fan unit ready to be installed on the roof.

Extracteurs de Toiture
Roof extractors delivered ready for connection and equipped with a protective grid on the discharge side.<SEP>Roof extractors that are to be fixed according to specifications.

Grille de Protection d'Accès
A protective grid on the discharge side of the roof extractor, conforming to DIN EN ISO 13857.

Côté Aspiration
The suction side of the roof extractor, which does not have a protective grid as standard.

Plaques Signalétiques
Nameplates containing technical specifications and permissible limit values.

Fiches Techniques
Technical data sheets containing technical specifications and permissible limit values.

Catalogues Correspondants
Relevant catalogs containing technical specifications and permissible limit values.

Extraction d'Air Propre
Extraction of clean air, gases, or non-aggressive vapors, which the roof extractors are suitable for.

Gaz ou Vapeurs Non Agressifs
Non-aggressive gases or vapors that the roof extractors are designed to handle.

Fluides Agressifs
Aggressive fluids that should not be transported by the extractors.

Fluides Très Poussiéreux
Very dusty fluids that should not be transported by the extractors.

Résonance
Resonance, a condition of high vibration to be avoided during operation.

Acides
Acids that could cause injury or damage if the extractors are misused.

Brûlures
Burns that could result from misuse of the extractors.

Fiche de Renseignements
A form to be used in case of transport damage.

Bloquer la Turbine
Blocked turbine caused by incorrect transport

Déformation de l’arbre
Deformation of the shaft caused by incorrect transport

Détérioration des Paliers
Damage to the bearings caused by incorrect transport

Oeillets de Suspensions
Suspension eyelets provided for lifting the roof extractors.

Dommages Corporels
Personal injury from falling extractors<SEP>Potential physical injuries that could result from prolonged incidents with the fan.

Humidité
The document describes the humidity conditions for storing the fan

Germany
Country where Wolf GmbH and Mainburg are located.<SEP>Germany is the country where Wolf GmbH is located.

Roof Extract Fan DV
English term for Dachventilatoren DV, refers to roof extract fans.<SEP>Roof Extract Fan DV is a product offered by Wolf GmbH, detailed in the installation, operation, and service instructions.<SEP>The Roof extract fan DV is the product for which the declaration of conformity is being issued.

Installation
Installation refers to the process of setting up and configuring the Roof Extract Fan DV.<SEP>Installation refers to the process of setting up the ventilators.<SEP>The complete installed system, any tension or vibration should not be transmitted to the ventilator.

Operation
Operation refers to the usage and functioning of the Roof Extract Fan DV.

Service
Service refers to the maintenance and support provided for the Roof Extract Fan DV.

Wartungspersonal
Maintenance personnel responsible for investigating malfunctions in the ventilator and performing repairs.<SEP>Maintenance personnel responsible for investigating malfunctions in the ventilator.<SEP>Wartungspersonal refers to maintenance personnel who are at risk if safety instructions are not followed.

Mobilen Kundendienst
Mobile customer service to be contacted if the maintenance personnel cannot fix the malfunction.

Ventilator
Ventilator refers to the fan that is being maintained and inspected.<SEP>Ventilator, a fan or ventilation device whose malfunctions are discussed in the text.<SEP>Ventilator, refers to a fan or ventilation device that can experience operational disturbances.

Anlageteile
Plant components that can be damaged due to prolonged disturbances in the ventilator.<SEP>Plant components that may be damaged as a result of ventilator malfunctions.

Betriebsstörungen
Operational disturbances or malfunctions in the ventilator's normal operating conditions.

Personenschäden
Personal injuries that may occur as a result of ventilator malfunctions.

Customer Field Service
Customer Field Service is offered by the company (likely ZDH) for faults that cannot be corrected by the user's service personnel.<SEP>Customer Field Service is offered by the company for faults that cannot be corrected by the user's service personnel.

Plant
Plant is mentioned in the context of potential damage from fan malfunctions.

DV 40 to 125
DV 40 to 125 is the product that the maintenance instructions are for. It is likely a fan or a component thereof.

Plant Components
Plant components are mentioned as being potentially damaged by fan malfunctions.

Service Personnel
Service personnel are individuals who perform maintenance, checks, and repairs on fans and related equipment. Their safety is a primary concern.<SEP>Service personnel are responsible for investigating malfunctions and performing maintenance.

Isolator
Isolator part of fan setup<SEP>The isolator is a component of the fan that needs to be checked for tension.

Silencer Casing
The silencer casing is a component of the fan that needs to be unfastened during disassembly.

Base Plate
The base plate is a component of the fan from which a bracket needs to be unfastened.

Motor Impeller
The motor and the impeller.<SEP>The motor impeller is a component of the fan that needs to be removed from the bracket.

Energieversorgungs-Unternehmen
The Energieversorgungs-Unternehmen is the responsible energy supply company that sets performance limits. Non-compliance can lead to power outages due to network overload.

DIN EN 563
DIN EN 563 is a safety standard defining the temperature limit for accessible parts of ventilators, requiring separating protective devices if exceeded.<SEP>DIN EN 563 refers to a safety standard related to the temperature of accessible elements on the fan. It specifies that protection systems must be in place if the temperature exceeds +70°C.<SEP>DIN EN 563 is a standard related to the surface temperature of accessible fans, setting a limit of +70°C.

DV 40 bis DV 125
DV 40 bis DV 125 is a model series of Wolf Dachventilatoren, featuring a V-housing made of galvanized sheet steel and a base frame for base mounting.<SEP>DV 40 bis DV 125 is a series of devices or models, possibly related to ventilation systems, mentioned in the context of cable routing and safety.

Revisionsschalter
A revision switch where voltage needs to be checked for freedom.<SEP>Revisionsschalter is a maintenance switch used to disconnect the motor from the power supply during maintenance and safety checks.<SEP>Revisionsschalter is a revision switch installed under the Wetterschutzhaube for maintenance and inspection of the ventilator.<SEP>Revisionsschalter refers to the maintenance or revision switch.<SEP>Revisionsschalter refers to the revision switch.<SEP>Revisionsschalter is a switch installed in the ventilator for maintenance and revision purposes.

Regenschutzhaube
A rain cover that needs to be removed.<SEP>Regenschutzhaube is a rain cover that protects electrical components like the maintenance switch from the elements.<SEP>Regenschutzhaube refers to the rain cover.

Thermokontakte
Thermokontakte are thermal contacts used in motors to protect against overheating by disconnecting power when a certain temperature is exceeded.

Motorvollschutz-Schaltgerät
Motorvollschutz-Schaltgerät is a motor protection device that protects the motor from damage due to overload or other electrical faults.

Schützkombination
Schützkombination is a contactor combination, an electromechanical switching device used for motor control and protection.

Schmelzsicherungen
Schmelzsicherungen are fuses used for overcurrent protection.

Sicherungsautomaten
Sicherungsautomaten are circuit breakers used for overcurrent protection.

Laufrad
Laufrad is the impeller or rotor of the ventilator.<SEP>Laufrad refers to the impeller of the ventilator.<SEP>Laufrad refers to the impeller or rotating wheel of the ventilator, whose standstill must be awaited due to the risk of injury from rotating parts.

VDMA 24 186-1
VDMA 24 186-1 is a standard related to service and checks of fans, defining the type, scope, and intervals of service actions.

GebhardtVentilatoren
GebhardtVentilatoren is a manufacturer of fans, who emphasizes the use of original spare parts and disclaims liability for damage from non-original parts.

Surface Temperature
The surface temperature of the fan, which poses no burning risk.

Residues
Damaging or dangerous residues left in the fan by the media conveyed.

Fan
A mechanical device used for ventilation and air circulation, subject to maintenance and safety checks.

Chapter 6
A chapter referring to commissioning and safety checks procedures.

Commissioning/ Safety Checks
The event of initiating and verifying the safe operation of a fan system.

Operating Mode
Specific condition in which the fan is running and performing its intended function, requiring adherence to safety regulations.

Vibration Measurement
The activity of measuring the vibration levels of a fan to assess its operational status.

Shock Pulse Measurement
The action of measuring the magnitude and characteristics of shocks or impacts within a fan system.

Service Actions
Tasks performed to maintain, repair, or inspect the fan and ensure its proper functionality.

Deposit
Accumulation of materials on fan components, which needs to be checked during maintenance.

Damages
Physical harm or deterioration of fan components that needs inspection.

Corrosion
Degradation of fan components due to chemical reactions, requiring monitoring and prevention.

Loose Parts
Components of the fan that are not securely fastened, potentially leading to malfunctions.

Impeller Balance
The state of equilibrium in the fan's impeller, affecting vibration and performance.

Flexible Connections
A component of the fans<SEP>Connectors that provides flexibility and isolation.

Tightness
The degree to which connections are secure and leak-proof.

AVM
Anti-vibration mounts.

Protections and Guards
Safety features designed to prevent contact with moving parts.

Drains
Components designed to remove fluids.<SEP>Part of the fan that removes fluids

Rotational Sense
The direction of rotation of the fan, essential for correct operation.

Regular Operation
The expected and normal functioning of the fan.

External Appearance
The visible condition of the fan's exterior, providing clues to its internal state.

Bearing Noise
Sound emitted by the fan's bearings, indicating potential wear or damage.

High Pressure Cleaner
A cleaning device that should not be used on the fan.

Short Circuits
An abnormal electrical connection that can damage the motor.

Motor Damages
Physical impairments on the motor.

Leaking Connectors
Connectors which are escaping media being conveyed.

Faults
Defects in the fan's operation or components.

Original Gebhardt Spare Parts
Replacement parts from Gebhardt.

Start Up/Safety Checks
The process of initiating the fan and verifying its safety.

Hazard
A potential source of danger to maintenance personnel.

Repair
The process of restoring a fan to working order.

Isolator Switch
A safety switch to disconnect the fan from the power supply.

Main Board
The electrical control panel for the fan.

Poles
Electrical connections.

Electrical Tension
Voltage.

Death
The end of life.

Fan Cowl
The cover of a fan.

Tension at Isolator
Voltage.

Grids
Parts of the fan.

Motor Connection Cable
A cable which connects the motor.

Motor Support
A component of the fans<SEP>A support of the motor.

Motor-Impeller Unit
Unit which includes the motor and the impeller.

Rain Protection Plate
A component of the fans<SEP>A plate that protects from the rain.

V Casing
